Overview
The current procedure for generating clinical reporting tables employs NEST packages such as {rtables}, {tern} and {chevron}. These packages create complex table structures and generate statistics that should be programmatically compared.
In this document, we will showcase how the {cards} and {cardx} packages can be used to QC common outputs generated using NEST packages.
